Telecommunications company Safaricom launched the 2017 edition of the &ldquo;This Is My Kenya&rdquo; initiative at the Kenyatta International Conference Centre in Nairobi.The initiative seeks to capture Kenya&rsquo;s beauty through the people&rsquo;s eyes.&ldquo;Capture the people you love, the food you eat, the places you visit and the life you live through the lens of your camera and share it with us,&rdquo; it reads.&ldquo;Let us celebrate our beautiful country and who we are as Kenyans,&rdquo; Safaricom CEO Bob Collymore said during the launch.The event was also attended by Tourism principal secretary Fatuma Hirsi Mohamed.